<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1898-10-07T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1898-10-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="794" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d794">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Day</persName> to the <gloss type="to">President</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1898-10-07"><hi rend="italic">October 7,
                                1898</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 5.]</seg></opener>
                        <p>Telegram received. In view of the answer made by us on Monday last [No.
                            1] with your approval to Spanish proposition as to status quo in
                            Philippines, we think we are precluded from presenting to Spanish
                            commissioners here any question properly belonging to two Governments,
                            or to the commissioners at Habana or San Juan. It would open to them a
                            door which by our answer of Monday we hoped we had closed finally.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Day.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>